================================================================================
Detection-stage references
================================================================================

PromptGuard's multi-stage detection pipeline integrates with the following
external projects. PromptGuard does not redistribute their code; it calls
them at runtime via documented interfaces.

  - OpenAI Privacy Filter (https://github.com/openai/privacy-filter), Apache 2.0,
    Copyright (c) 2026 OpenAI. PromptGuard runs OPF as a separate FastAPI
    container that wraps the HuggingFace `openai/privacy-filter` model. See
    src/promptguard/services/opf_service/.
  - Microsoft Presidio (https://github.com/microsoft/presidio), MIT License,
    Copyright (c) Microsoft Corporation. PromptGuard talks to the Presidio
    analyzer over HTTP. See src/promptguard/detectors/presidio.py.

================================================================================
Benchmark-corpus references (cited, not redistributed)
================================================================================

PromptGuard's benchmarks reference the following corpora. The corpora
themselves are not included in this repository.

  - AI4Privacy PII-Masking-300k (https://huggingface.co/datasets/ai4privacy/pii-masking-300k).
    License: "other" (academic evaluation use without separate licensing;
    commercial training requires licensing). PromptGuard runs the v1.1.1
    detection benchmarks against the English validation split of this
    corpus and reports per-category F1 in docs/benchmarks.md. We use the
    corpus for evaluation only; we do not train on it; we do not
    redistribute any corpus content here. SHA256 manifests of locally
    cached files live in local/benchmarks/corpora/ai4privacy/manifest.txt
    so the methodology is reproducible from a clean checkout.
  - GitHub Issues Secrets Benchmark (https://arxiv.org/abs/2410.23657,
    https://zenodo.org/records/17430336). License: Creative Commons
    Attribution 4.0 International (CC-BY 4.0). Citation:
    "Secret Leak Detection in Software Issue Reports using LLMs:
    A Comprehensive Evaluation," arxiv 2410.23657. PromptGuard
    runs the v1.1.1 detection benchmarks against the test_wild split
    of this corpus and reports per-category numbers in docs/benchmarks.md.
    We do not redistribute the corpus.
  - Tonic.ai OpenAI Privacy Filter benchmark
    (https://www.tonic.ai/blog/benchmarking-openai-privacy-filter-pii-detection).
    Numbers cited as the external sanity check on OPF operating points;
    no benchmark content redistributed.

